The paper discusses the use of network graphs to represent and analyze functional interactions between multiple neural sources, which is a topic within computational neuroscience (cs.NE). The paper also proposes an algorithmic approach to handle the intractability of multivariate interaction reconstruction, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of graph metrics to analyze the resulting networks, which is a topic within social network analysis (cs.SI) and statistical learning (cs.SD).
